SUMMARY:Spring Fling Wine Tasting at Stuhlmuller Vineyards
DESCRIPTION:Sonoma County Women's Wine Club (SCWWC)\nSpring has sprung her
 e in wine country!\n\nI have the pleasure of setting up a fantastic wine t
 asting at Stuhlmuller Vineyards in Geyserville.\n\nIf you haven't been to 
 Stuhlmuller Vineyards\, you are in for a treat. They are a spacious and un
 ique winery open to the public\, with a tasting room and vineyards in Alex
 ander Valley. They specialize in Pinot Noir\, Cabernet Sauvignon\, Zinfand
 el\, and Chardonnay. You are welcome to purchase wine outside of the tasti
 ng provided.\n\nThere is a maximum of 15 spots available\, and this is a C
 o-ed event\, so both men and women are welcome.\n\nThe cost of the event i
 s $26\, which includes the wine tasting\, plus our club slush fund fee of 
 $1. They likely will waive the tasting fee with the purchase of wine bottl
 es\, or by becoming members of their wine club.\n\nGuests are welcome. I s
 uggest you wear layers as we will be outside\, and sometimes the weather i
 s windy or cold. Please allow extra time to get there\, the vineyard is ab
 out 5 miles from the Highway 101 exit at Lytton. We will confirm headcount
  about a week before.\n\nCheers to this fun relaxing event!
