BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Women's Wine Club
UID:event_312553959@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260410T031046Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T190000
SUMMARY:THIRSTY THURSDAY New Member Social for Sonoma County Women's Wine 
 Club
DESCRIPTION:Sonoma County Women's Wine Club (SCWWC)\nThis is our regular c
 lub meeting\, held on the last Thursday of every month except for holidays
  and we are super excited! Come join us at 4th Street Cellars in downtown 
 Santa Rosa. They have generously offered to host our monthly THIRSTY THURS
 DAY social for us.\n\nIf you are new to the area\, or just looking to get 
 out of the house and make new friends\, this is the place for you. Welcomi
 ng to ALL new and (ahem\, old) members.\n\nWine is purchased by the glass 
 for a set fee of $13/$14 per glass with the variety of white\, rosé\, and
  red wines offered through 4th Street Cellars which includes tip. Fees are
  collected at the venue by Co-organizer Daima Phipps via cash\, Venmo\, or
  Paypal. You are welcome to purchase wine separately if you choose. Starti
 ng March 2025\, we ask that every attending member pay a $1 "slush" fund f
 ee per event so that we can build up our funds for club-related expenses\,
  which can be paid by Venmo or cash.\n\nThere is no food offered\, but you
  are welcome to bring an appetizer or snack to share with the group\, and 
 many ladies do. We will have time to socialize while tasting in the room u
 pstairs to the left or the outside patio if the weather is nice.\n\nThe sp
 ace has a 25 person attendee limit\, but the list is open to 40 to elimina
 te a waitlist\, and guests are welcome! Please RSVP below only if you are 
 able to make it\, we have an attendance policy: if you No-Show to three ev
 ents\, you may not attend events for the next three months. Please put thi
 s event in your calendar so you don't miss out or get dinged. A No-Show is
  when you are on the 'Going' list\, but do not show up.\n\nSee you there\,
  ready to kickoff!
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/sonoma-county-womens-wine-club/events
 /312553959/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251223T201100Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251223T201100Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Women's Wine Club
UID:event_313060290@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260410T031046Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T150000
SUMMARY:A Wine & Garden Party Fit for Mrs. Roper
DESCRIPTION:Sonoma County Women's Wine Club (SCWWC)\nQuirky\, fun\, and al
 ways dressed with comfort and flair\, Mrs. Roper was a vibe.\n\n**Event De
 tails**\nWine Tasting & small\nBites $25 per person. Fee paid directly to 
 winery on day of event.\n\n**Theme & Dress Code ideas:**\n•Flowy colorfu
 l muumuus\n•Big sunglasses\n•Costume jewelry\n•Wigs or turbans\nTher
 e may be games & prizes 😎\n\nAmazon is a great site for all your Mrs. R
 oper needs!\n\nAbout Smith-Story winery:\nSmith Story Wine Cellars\, based
  in Sonoma County\, is the labor of love for Eric and Alison\, who bring t
 heir combined 40+ years in the wine industry to the venture. Born out of t
 heir shared passion for wines during their tenure at K&L Wine Merchants\, 
 the couple founded the winery after eloping in Hawaii in 2013. Eric’s ex
 pertise lies in wine buying and retail management\, specifically in Europe
 an wines\, while Ali excels in hospitality\, marketing\, and sales\, provi
 ding a complete wine-supply-chain approach. Respect for the land and love 
 for winemaking guide their philosophy\, as they utilize old world techniqu
 es in creating balanced and expressive wines from family-owned vineyards. 
 Acting with kindness for the grower and commitment to quality\, Smith Stor
 y Wine Cellars embodies the vision of its founders to create wines that en
 capsulate their journey and passion.
