SUMMARY:Give 'Em the Axe! Ladies Night at the Range in Santa Rosa
DESCRIPTION:Sonoma County Women's Wine Club (SCWWC)\nJoin us for an axe-th
 rowing session to blow off some steam. I'm super excited to be able to off
 er a ladies' Axe-throwing night in Santa Rosa. If you've ever had a curios
 ity about this fun activity\, this is your chance to find out more!\n\nWe 
 have reserved a group spot with the indoor range on a Wednesday night. It 
 will consist of an introductory lesson\, and then we all get to practice t
 aking turns. Everyone will get ample time to practice\, as they have many 
 lanes.\n\nThis event is focused on a less-competitive\, relaxed\, and ente
 rtaining atmosphere. All skill levels are encouraged. All equipment and ta
 rgets are provided by them\, and we will probably get about 1 to 2 hours t
 o enjoy ourselves.\n\nI encourage everyone to bring a bottle of wine or a 
 snack to share with the rest of the group (We usually end up with a lovely
  charcuterie and wine spread for everyone to enjoy).\n\nThere are 10 spots
  available\, guests welcome. The ladies' group lesson and event is $30 per
 son\, paid to the range. Starting March 2025\, we ask that every attending
  member pay a $1 "slush" fund fee per event so that we can build up our fu
 nds for club-related expenses\, which can be paid by Venmo or cash. There 
 may be standard liability forms to be filled out with the range. Closed-to
 ed shoes are recommended.\n\nPlease only RSVP 'Yes' if you are able to mak
 e it\, hostess Dai Phipps will be collecting a $5 fee via Venmo to hold yo
 ur spot. She will follow up with everyone who RSVP's 'Yes' via direct mess
 age or you may pay the $5 through the enclosed Venmo link. Returns cannot 
 be accommodated after the Sunday before the event. Here is the link: [www.
 venmo.com/Daima-Phipps](http://www.venmo.com/Daima-Phipps)\n\nThere is an 
 attendance policy for all our events: if you No-Show to three events\, you
  may not attend events for the next three months. Please put this event in
  your calendar so you don't miss out or get dinged. A No-Show is when you 
 are on the 'Going' list\, but do not show up.\n\nCheers\, and hope to see 
 you there!
